---
import StepList from "../StepList.astro";
import Step from "../Step.astro";
import { CodeBlock } from "../CodeBlock.tsx";
---

<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pb-32">
  <div class="mb-10 text-center">
    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">
      Quick Start
    </h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 text-lg">
      From operator install to your first allowed-vs-denied tool call.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-6 p-4 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-500/[0.06] border border-emerald-500/20 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm text-emerald-200/90">
        End-to-end L7 <span class="font-mono">MCPEgressPolicy</span> enforcement needs
        operator <span class="font-mono">v0.14.0+</span> (which ships the
        <span class="font-mono">MCPEgressPolicy</span> CRD and its controller) and core
        <span class="font-mono">v1.6.0+</span> (the L7 evaluator). Both are released, so
        the steps below run end-to-end today. On operator
        <span class="font-mono">v0.13.0</span> only the admission webhooks and the
        default-deny L3/L4 egress backstop apply — the L7 tool rules require
        <span class="font-mono">v0.14.0+</span>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <StepList>
      <Step
        number={1}
        title="Install the operator"
        description="Install the MCP-Hangar Operator with Helm. It brings the CRDs — including MCPEgressPolicy — and reconciles policy into the cluster."
      >
        <CodeBlock client:load language="bash">{`helm install mcp-hangar-operator \\
  oci://ghcr.io/mcp-hangar/charts/mcp-hangar-operator \\
  --namespace mcp-hangar --create-namespace \\
  --set hangar.url=http://mcp-hangar-core:8080

kubectl get pods -n mcp-hangar`}</CodeBlock>
      </Step>

      <Step
        number={2}
        title="Opt a namespace into enforcement"
        description="Label the target namespace so the default-deny egress backstop is in place — the backstop is what makes the policy enforcement rather than a suggestion."
      >
        <CodeBlock client:load language="bash">{`kubectl label namespace prod mcp-hangar.io/enforce-egress=true`}</CodeBlock>
      </Step>

      <Step
        number={3}
        title="Apply an egress policy"
        description="Deny by default; allow only read-only GitHub tools and pin egress to a single upstream. Enforce mode blocks everything else."
      >
        <CodeBlock client:load language="yaml">{`# gh-only.yaml
apiVersion: mcp-hangar.io/v1alpha2
kind: MCPEgressPolicy
metadata:
  name: gh-only
  namespace: prod
spec:
  mode: Enforce            # Audit observes; Enforce blocks
  targetRef:
    kind: MCPServer
    name: srv
  defaultAction: Deny      # tool names no rule matches are denied
  upstreams:
    - name: github
      match:
        host: api.github.com
      tools:
        allow: ["get_*", "list_*"]`}</CodeBlock>
        <div class="mt-3">
          <CodeBlock client:load language="bash">{`kubectl apply -f gh-only.yaml`}</CodeBlock>
        </div>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-xs mt-3">
          The tool allow/deny rules enforce on any cluster. Pinning egress to an
          <span class="text-zinc-400">FQDN</span> upstream like <code class="text-zinc-400">api.github.com</code>
          at the network layer needs the Cilium backstop flavor — on a vanilla cluster, use a CIDR upstream instead.
        </p>
      </Step>

      <Step
        number={4}
        title="See allowed vs denied"
        description="Confirm the policy compiled and the network backstop is live. Read-only calls now pass; everything else fails closed before it reaches the upstream."
        isLast
      >
        <CodeBlock client:load language="bash">{`$ kubectl -n prod get mcpegresspolicy gh-only \\
    -o jsonpath='{range .status.conditions[*]}{.type}={.status}{"\\n"}{end}'
Compiled=True
BackstopApplied=True
Degraded=False`}</CodeBlock>
        <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20">
          <span class="text-emerald-400 text-lg">[ok]</span>
          <span class="text-emerald-300 font-medium">get_* / list_* allowed · everything else denied · egress pinned to api.github.com</span>
        </div>
      </Step>
    </StepList>
  </div>
</section>
